  "hypothesis": "Mid-air benchmark reveals policy never learned navigation \u2014 even starting 0.75m from gate (matching training spawn exactly), 0 gates passed in all runs. Root cause: one-sided progress reward max(prev_dist - dist, 0) only rewards getting closer but has ZERO penalty for moving away. The policy collects reward from stochastic movements that happen to get closer, while the deterministic mean drifts in arbitrary directions. Fix: bilateral_progress=true uses raw delta (prev_dist - dist) so moving AWAY from the gate is penalized. This creates a proper gradient toward the gate for the deterministic mean.",
